news.title: Bankruptcy court allows 90 days extension to revive Lavasa Corporation
news.para: The planned city project is undergoing a fresh Corporate Insolvency Resolution Process (CIRP) after the National Company Law Tribunal directed to restart the whole process after the successful bidder failed to implement the approved resolution plan within the timeline.

news.title: Delhi HC declines immediate relief to Okhla slum dwellers
news.para: A bench of Chief Justice Devendra Upadhyay and Justice Tushar Rao Gedela declined to hear the appeal filed by the locals on Wednesday itself but indicated it would be automatically listed on Thursday if documents were in order.

news.title: Mumbai: MMRDA lodges FIR against illegal occupants of 1,336 Kurla homes
news.para: Last year, MMRDA had issued eviction notices to the illegal occupants. MMRDA had also sought more than Rs 35 cr in rental arrears with GST from them.

news.title: NCLT freezes Ansal API's bank accounts
news.para: This development marks a crucial step in the insolvency process of Ansal API, with further actions expected in the coming weeks. The receiver's team is also compiling records of home and plot bookings.

news.title: Bihar CM releases Rs 1,200 crore as first instalment of PMAY-Gramin
news.para: During the programme, rural development department (RDD) secretary, Lokesh Kumar Singh informed through a presentation that the state govt got a target of construction of 2,43,903 houses under the PMAY-G in Sept 2024 from the Centre.

news.title: Telangana RERA fines TMR Marvel's builder for deficit amenities
news.para: According to the complaint, Sravanthi entered into an agreement with the developers on Feb 5, 2018, to purchase a semi-finished villa.

news.title: Telangana RERA orders Padmasreekar Icon's builder to fix defects, pay fine
news.para: In its order dated March 1, the authority directed the builder to pay a penalty of 4.5 lakh and rectify defects in the flats at Padmasreekar Icon, Gajularamaram of Medchal-Malkajgiri.

news.title: Chennai civic body issues exhaustive guidelines to prevent construction pollution
news.para: In a preemptive effort, GCC has come out with exhaustive guidelines mandating builders to place barricades, cover construction sites with metal sheets to prevent dust from spilling, use anti-smog guns and to ensure vehicles carrying debris are covered with tarpaulin sheets.

news.title: LIC Housing Finance board approves Rs 1.23 lakh crore borrowing budget for FY26
news.para: Based on the recommendation by the audit committee, the board has approved the borrowing budget aggregate to Rs 1,22,500 crore for financial year 2025-2026, the company said in a stock exchange filing.

news.title: Another FIR lodged against Ansal Group in Ghaziabad
news.para: In the FIR, Pranav Ansal, Vikas Yadav, general manager Amit Shukla and other officials of the firm have been booked under Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita (BNS) sections 318(4) (cheating), 338 (forgery of valuable security, will etc.), 336(3) (forgery for cheating), 61(2) (criminal conspiracy) and section 3 of the Prevention of Damage to Public Property Act, police said.

news.title: Belagavi city corporation receives Rs 135 crore under smart city project
news.para: Recently, a quadrilateral agreement was signed between the Union ministry of urban development, and state representative KUIDFC Bengaluru, Smart city Belagavi, and Belagavi city corporation.

news.title: Jammu and Kashmir CM unveils multiple smart city projects
news.para: In addition to highlighting the need for widespread exposure to promote Jammu's distinctive sites, the Chief Minister noted the difficulties in drawing pilgrims outside of Vaishno Devi.

news.title: Demand for quality office space leads to increase in pre-bookings
news.para: At present, India is facing a shortage of approximately 20 million sq. ft. of Grade A+ office space annually, as demand for quality office space continues to outstrip supply, said Cushman & Wakefield.

news.title: Mumbai: Tesla to rent space from Maker Group for Rs 881 per sq ft per month
news.para: The showroom is expected to serve as a flagship destination for Tesla’s operations in India, signalling the brand’s commitment to catering to the country’s growing demand for premium electric vehicles.

news.title: Noida: Three people arrested for allegedly forging documents to sell Rs 95 crore property
news.para: DCP (central Noida) Shakti Mohan Avasthy said Mujahid Hussain, president of the Dasna Nagar panchayat, alerted Bisrakh police on Feb 28.

news.title: Housing minister expresses satisfaction over progress of central schemes in Bihar
news.para: "The Union minister expressed satisfaction over the progress of various schemes of the Housing and Urban Affairs Department and works being carried out by the state government departments in Bihar."

news.title: UK's Balfour Beatty appoints Philip Hoare as CEO
news.para: Hoare joins Balfour Beatty from Canadian engineering services group AtkinsRealis, where he was chief operating officer for a year after leading the UK and global engineering businesses.

news.title: Pune: PCB to revise building bylaws for its civil and bungalow areas
news.para: The move will decide the fate of construction activity in the cantonment areas, sprawling over 2,954 acres of land, of which at least 250 acres are in the civil pockets.

news.title: Housing finance market to grow at 15-16% CAGR through 2029-30: CareEdge
news.para: CareEdge Ratings believes that this growth will be driven by robust structural elements and favourable government incentives, making housing finance an attractive asset class for lenders.

news.title: Blackstone may acquire South City Mall in Kolkata for up to $400 million
news.para: The shopping mall is owned by South City Projects (Kolkata) Ltd., a joint venture of several real estate developers based in the city, and is the largest in eastern India, according to its website.
